        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Land for David G. Richardson on which he pays fees and gets a share. Mrs. Holley. Loan</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><placeName>Columbia</placeName>, <date when="1835-05-08">8th May 1835</date></p>

<p><persName>Mr Gaile Borden</persName></p>

<p><placeName>land office</placeName></p>

<p>This will be handed to you by <persName>Mr. David S Richardson</persName> a respectable and
<persName>industrious man of family</persName> [for whom Austin wants land.] . . .</p>

<p>I go below <date when="1835-05-08">to day</date> with my horses for <persName>Mrs. Holley</persName> and on return shall
visit <placeName>St Filipe</placeName> as soon as practicable I have arranged for a loan of
3000$ which will enable me to close my acct of fees with the <placeName>office </placeName>by
paying any balance which may appear on settlement with <persName>Col A</persName> or
<persName>Williams</persName></p>

<p><persName>H. Austin</persName> [Rubric]</p>

<p><persName>Henry Austin</persName> to <persName>Gail Borden, Jr.</persName></p>


        </div1>
    </body>
